    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <div>
      <p>I am a Professor in the <a href="https://www.cse.ohio-state.edu/">Department of Computer Science and Engineering</a> at <a href="https://www.osu.edu/">Ohio State University</a>. I lead the <strong><a href="research.html">Architecture Research Lab</a></strong>. Our research interests include computer architecture, energy efficient computing, security and reliability. </p>
      <p>I received my Ph.D. from the <a href="https://cs.illinois.edu/">Department of Computer Science</a>, <a href="https://illinois.edu/">University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign</a> where I was a member of the <a href="http://iacoma.cs.uiuc.edu/">IACOMA</a> group working with <a href="http://iacoma.cs.uiuc.edu/~torrella/">Prof. Josep Torrellas</a>. I was the recipient of the Ohio State CSE Department Teaching Award in 2021, the <a href="https://engineering.osu.edu/awards/content/lumley-research-award">Lumley Award</a> in 2014, an <a href="https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=1253933&HistoricalAwards=false">NSF CAREER award</a> in 2012, <a href="https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/education/highered/higher-ed-overview.html">Intel Foundation Fellowship</a> for 2007-2008 and the <a href="https://cs.illinois.edu/csillinois/awards#2007-2008">W. J. Poppelbaum Award</a> for 2008. We were proud to help organize <a href="https://www.microarch.org/micro52/">MICRO-52 in Columbus, Ohio</a> in October 2019.</p>
